## Definitions

- Let $\by = (y_1, \ldots, y_p)^\top \in\{0,1\}^p$ be a vector of Bernoulli random variables.

- The joint probability of observing any response pattern $\bc_r=(c_{r1},\dots,c_{rp})^\top$, for any $r=1,\dots,R:=2^p$, is given by
$$
\pi_r = \Pr(\by = \bc_r) = \Pr(y_1=c_{r1},\dots,y_p=c_{rp}).
$${#eq-joint-bern-prob}
and $\sum_{r=1}^R \pi_r = 1$.

- Suppose $h=1,\dots,n$ observations of $\by=\by^{(h)}$ are recorded, and each unit has a probability of selection $1/w_h$. 

- Out of convenience, sampling weights are (typically) normalised so that $\sum_{h=1}^n w_h = n$.
  - Simple random sampling (SRS): $w_h=1, \forall h$.
  - Stratified sampling: $w_h = N_s(h)/N$, the stratum fractions.
  - Etc.

## Multinomial distribution

- Let $p_r = \hat n_r \big/ \sum_h w_h$ be the the $r$th entry of the $R$-vector of proportions $\bp$, with $\hspace{1.4cm}$
$$
\hat n_r = \sum_{h=1}^n w_h [\by^{(h)} = \bc_r].
$${#eq-obs-freq}

::: {.nudge-up-large}
- The random vector $\hat\bn = (\hat n_1,\dots,\hat n_R)^\top$ follows a multinomial distribution with parameters $n$, $R$, and $\bpi:=(\pi_1,\dots,\pi_R)^\top$.
:::

::: {.nudge-up-xxl}
$$
\E(\hat\bn) = n\bp = n\bpi \hspace{2em}\text{and}\hspace{2em} \Var(\hat\bn) = n\big( \ \myoverbrace{\diag(\bpi) - \bpi\bpi^\top}{\bSigma} \ \big)
$$
:::

::: {.nudge-up-xxl}
- It is widely known that [@agresti2012categorical] for IID samples that
$$
\sqrt n (\bp - \bpi) \xrightarrow{\text D} {\N}_R(\bzero, \bSigma)
$${#eq-multin-clt}
as $n\to\infty$. This also works for complex sampling [@fuller2009introduction], but $\bSigma$ may take a different form.

:::

## Parametric models


::: {.columns}

::: {.column width=37%}

![](figures/sem_path.png)

:::

::: {.column width=63%}

::: {.absolute top=25}
- E.g. binary factor model with underlying variable approach (s.t. constraints)
$$
\begin{gathered}
y_i = \begin{cases}
1 & y_i^* > \tau_i \\
0 & y_i^* \leq \tau_i
\end{cases} \\
\by^* = \bLambda\bfeta + \bepsilon \\
\bfeta \sim {\N}_q(\bzero, \bPsi), \hspace{3pt}
\bepsilon \sim {\N}_p(\bzero, \bTheta_{\epsilon})
\end{gathered}
$${#eq-facmod}
:::

::: {.fragment fragment-index=1 .absolute top=355}
- The log-likelihood for 
$\btheta^\top = ($[$\blambda$]{.ubdred}$,$[$\brho$]{.ubdteal}$,$[$\btau$]{.ubdblue}$)$ is $\hspace{3.8cm}$
$$
\log L(\btheta \mid \by) = \sum_{r=1}^R \hat n_r \log \pi_r(\btheta)
$${#eq-facmod-loglik}
where $\pi_r(\btheta) = \int \phi_p(\by^* \mid \bzero, \bLambda\bPsi\bLambda^\top + \bTheta_\epsilon) \dint \by^*$.
:::

