## Pairwise likelihood estimation

- For pairs of variables $y_i$ and $y_j$, $i,j=1,\dots,n$, and $i<j$, define $\hspace{5cm}$ 
$$
\pi_{cc'}^{(ij)}(\btheta) = \Pr_{\btheta}(y_i = c, y_i = c'), \hspace{2em} c,c'\in\{0,1\}.
$${#eq-pairwise}
There are $\tilde R = 4 \times \binom{p}{2}$ such probabilities, with $\sum_{y_i,y_j} \pi_{y_iy_j}^{(ij)}(\btheta) = 1$.

- The pairwise log-likelihood takes the form [@katsikatsou2012pairwise]
$$
\log \pL(\btheta \mid \by) = \sum_{i<j} \sum_{c}\sum_{c'} \hat n_{cc'}^{(ij)} \log \pi_{y_iy_j}^{(ij)}(\btheta),
$${#eq-pairwise-loglik}
where $\hat n_{cc'}^{(ij)} = \sum_h w_h [\by^{(h)}_i = c, \by^{(h)}_j = c']$.

- Evaluation of @eq-pairwise-loglik involves only bivariate normal integrals:
$$
\pi_{cc'}^{(ij)}(\btheta) = \int\int \phi_2\big(\by^*_{ij} \mid \bzero, \bSigma_{y^*}^{(ij)} (\btheta)\big) \dint \by^*_{ij},
$$

## MPLE properties

- Let $\mlepl = \argmax_{\btheta} \pL(\btheta \mid \by)$. Under certain regularity conditions, [@varin2011overview]
$$
\sqrt n (\mlepl - \btheta) \xrightarrow{\text D} {\N}_m
\left(
\bzero, 
\left\{ \cH(\btheta)\cJ(\btheta)^{-1}\cH(\btheta) \right\}^{-1}
\right),\hspace{1em} \text{where}
$${#eq-asymptotic-mple}
   - $\cH(\btheta)=-\E\nabla^2\log \pL(\btheta \mid \by^{(h)})$ is the *sensitivity matrix*; and
   - $\cJ(\btheta)=\Var\big(\nabla\log\pL(\btheta \mid \by^{(h)})\big)$ is the *variability matrix*.

- Estimators of these matrices are given by [@zhao.joe05;@asparouhov2005sampling]
$$
\begin{aligned}
\bH &= - \frac{1}{\sum_h w_h} \sum_h \nabla^2\log \pL(\btheta \mid \by^{(h)}) \Bigg|_{\btheta = \mlepl} \hspace{2em}\text{and} \\
\bJ &= \frac{1}{\sum_h w_h} \sum_h \nabla\log \pL(\btheta \mid \by^{(h)}) \nabla\log \pL(\btheta \mid \by^{(h)})^T \Bigg|_{\btheta = \mlepl}.
\end{aligned}
$${#eq-hessian}

